==English==
===Etymology===
From German [[Weltanschauung]]

===Noun===
'''weltanschauung''' (plural [[weltanschauungs]] or [[weltanschauungen]])

#A [[comprehensive]] [[conception]], [[apprehension]] or [[view]] of the [[world]], especially from a specific [[standpoint]]; a [[worldview]]
#: ''Your background and experiences must give you a unique '''weltanschauung'''.''

One's weltanschauung is one's fundamental beliefs about the world and life. In English the term is often represented by the phrase "world and life view."
